'''男性內褲指數'''（英语: '''men's underwear index'''，簡稱'''MUI'''）是一種可以偵測[[经济衰退|经济衰退]]之後的[[經濟復甦|復甦]]的{{link-en|經濟指數|Index (economics)}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://bschool.hexun.com/2014-09-24/168752040.html |title=十大另类经济指标 |access-date=2014-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304131724/http://bschool.hexun.com/2014-09-24/168752040.html |archive-date=2016-03-04 |dead-url=yes }}</REF>。其理論是男性[[內褲|內褲]]在一般經濟情形下是必需品，銷售量相對穩定。但若是嚴重经济衰退，男性內褲的購買意願就會下降<ref>{{cite news|last=Mui|first=Ylan Q.|title=Blue Chip, White Cotton: What Underwear Says About the Economy|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/08/30/AR2009083002761.html|accessdate=1 February 2011|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=31 August 2009|archive-date=2014-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140719132556/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/08/30/AR2009083002761.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。因此男性內褲銷量可以反映{{link-en|可自由支配開支|Discretionary spending}}的提高，特別是在经济衰退之後的時間。

男性內褲指數是由前[[聯邦準備理事會|聯邦準備理事會]]主席[[艾伦·格林斯潘|艾伦·格林斯潘]]所發現<ref>{{cite news|last=Brush|first=Michael|title=How your undies track the recession|url=http://articles.moneycentral.msn.com/Investing/CompanyFocus/how-your-undies-track-the-recession.aspx|accessdate=1 February 2011|newspaper=MSN Money|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110302061931/http://articles.moneycentral.msn.com/Investing/CompanyFocus/how-your-undies-track-the-recession.aspx|archive-date=2011-03-02|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

